90","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Skotland"},"nl":{"Abt 1270–Abt 1320":"circa 1270–circa 1320","1270–1320":"1270–1320","–Female":"Overleden","1300–1372":"1300–1372","1240–1290":"1240–1290","1240–Female":"1240–Overleden","Abt 1300":"circa 1300","before 1300":"vóór 1300","1300":"1300","Abt 1320":"circa 1320","1320":"1320","before 1240":"vóór 1240","1240":"1240","1372":"1372","Abt 1270":"circa 1270","1270":"1270","Abt 1290":"circa 1290","1290":"1290","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Scotland":"Schotland"},"en":{"Abt 1270–Abt 1320":"about 1270–about 1320","1270–1320":"1270–1320","–Female":"Deceased","1300–1372":"1300–1372","1240–1290":"1240–1290","1240–Female":"1240–Deceased","Abt 1300":"about 1300","before 1300":"before 1300","1300":"1300","Abt 1320":"about 1320","1320":"1320","before 1240":"before 1240","1240":"1240","1372":"1372","Abt 1270":"about 1270","1270":"1270","Abt 1290":"about 1290","1290":"1290","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Innes","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: shortened form of   McInnis  , from Gaelic <b>Mag Aonghuis</b> ‘son of Aonghus’.","Scottish: habitational name from the barony of Innes in Urquhart (Morayshire), named from Gaelic <i>inis</i> ‘island’.","English: variant of   Ince  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Inniss","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Innes  ."]},{"name":"Ince","meanings":["habitational name from Ince in Makerfield (Lancashire), Ince (Cheshire), or Ince Blundell (Lancashire). The placenames derive from Proto-Welsh <i>ïnïs</i> ‘island’.","possibly a post-medieval West Midlands variant of <b>Hints</b>, a habitational name from either of two places called Hints (Staffordshire, Shropshire). The placenames probably derive from Proto-Welsh <i>hïnt</i> ‘way, path’ + Middle English plural <i>-es</i>.","possibly a variant with plural or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i> of <i>Inn</i>, from residence at an <i>inn</i> or <i>inns</i>, from Middle English <i>in</i> (singular) or <i>innes</i> (plural) ‘tavern, lodging(s), tenement(s)’. There seems also to have been some confusion with Scottish   Innes  ."]},{"name":"Inch","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Innes  .","English: perhaps, at least in some cases, a variant of   Ince  .","English: variant of   Hinch  ."]},{"name":"McInnis","meanings":["Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Aonghuis</b>, a patronymic from the personal name <i>Aonghus</i> (see   Angus  ). See also   McInnes  , compare Irish   McGinnis  ."]},{"name":"Innis","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Innes  .","English: variant of   Ince  ."]},{"name":"Inness","meanings":["Scottish (Durham and Northumberland): variant of   Innes  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William de Innes 6th of Innes - of that Ilk was born about 1270, his father, William de Innes 5th of Innes - of that Ilk, was 32 and his mother, Lady William de Innes, V, was 32. He married Lady William de Innes, VI before 1300, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1320, at the age of 52."},"et":{"Abt 1270–Abt 1320":"umbes 1270–umbes 1320","1270–1320":"1270–1320","–Female":"Surnud","1300–1372":"1300–1372","1240–1290":"1240–1290","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","Abt 1300":"umbes 1300","before 1300":"enne 1300","1300":"1300","Abt 1320":"umbes 1320","1320":"1320","before 1240":"enne 1240","1240":"1240","1372":"1372","Abt 1270":"umbes 1270","1270":"1270","Abt 1290":"umbes 1290","1290":"1290","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"Abt 1270–Abt 1320":"noin 1270–noin 1320","1270–1320":"1270–1320","–Female":"Kuollut","1300–1372":"1300–1372","1240–1290":"1240–1290","1240–Female":"1240–Kuollut","Abt 1300":"noin 1300","before 1300":"ennen vuotta 1300","1300":"1300","Abt 1320":"noin 1320","1320":"1320","before 1240":"ennen vuotta 1240","1240":"1240","1372":"1372","Abt 1270":"noin 1270","1270":"1270","Abt 1290":"noin 1290","1290":"1290","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"Abt 1270–Abt 1320":"environ 1270–environ 1320","1270–1320":"1270–1320","–Female":"Décédée","1300–1372":"1300–1372","1240–1290":"1240–1290","1240–Female":"1240–Décédée","Abt 1300":"environ 1300","before 1300":"avant 1300","1300":"1300","Abt 1320":"environ 1320","1320":"1320","before 1240":"avant 1240","1240":"1240","1372":"1372","Abt 1270":"environ 1270","1